    "Based on these principles, it is clear that protection systems must be fast enough and selective enough to isolate faults without affecting the entire network, thereby improving power system reliability.",
    "On the other hand, system protection response to abnormal operating conditions affecting a wider area.",
    "In both cases, the protection schemes should avoid excessive complexity.",
